Ronan Ghosh stole £200 worth of meat and wine from a Tesco store in Birmingham . 
  He heads a global recycling company with a turnover of £16million and lives in a £500,000 home . 
  The 39-year-old was filmed attempting to smuggle the goods out of the store in a bag . 
  He was given a 12-month community order and must pay £575 in costs . 
  Court heard he was caught shoplifting after an argument with his girlfriend . 
  He initially elected trial by jury but then pleaded guilty to theft . 
  Judge Murray Creed told him to complete 80 hours’ unpaid work . 
 